<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
MORTGAGES, MORTGAGE BANKERS, MORTGAGE-BACKED SECURITIES (MOR)
</IN>
<LP>
   The following were among yesterday's offerings and
pricings in U.S. and non-U.S. capital markets, with terms and
syndicate manager, as compiled by Dow Jones Capital Markets
Report: Report:
                                                                                                       

                          CORPORATE
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   Southern New England Telephone -- $100 million of 9.60%
notes, due Feb. 15, 2030, was priced at 98.50 to yield
9.751%. The notes were priced at a spread of 1.19 percentage
points above the Treasury's 30-year bond. Rated double-A-1 by
Moody's Investors Service Inc. and double-A-plus by Standard
&amp; Poor's Corp., the issue will be sold through underwriters
led by Salomon Brothers Inc.
                                                                                                       

                         MUNICIPALS
                                                                                                       

   Washington Suburban Sanitary District, Md. -- $90 million
of various purpose revenue bonds, due June 1, 1992-2014,
apparently were won by a Clayton Brown &amp; Associates Inc.
group with a bid setting the true interest cost at 6.90%. The
issue, commonly called "Wash Tubs," contains four types of
bonds: $39 million of general construction bonds, $31 million
of water supply bonds, $10 million of sewage disposal bonds
and $10 million of administration building construction
bonds. The bonds, rated double-A-1 by Moody's Investors
Service Inc. and double-A by Standard &amp; Poor's Corp., were
priced for reoffering to yield from 6.00% in 1992 to 7.00% in
2009-2012. Bonds maturing in 2013 and 2014 weren't formally
reoffered. There are no term bonds.
   Essex County, N.J. -- $65 million of improvement authority
county general obligation bonds and lease revenue bonds,
Series 1990, due Dec. 1, 1993-2004, 2010 and 2020, were
tentatively priced by an A.G. Edwards &amp; Sons Inc. group to
yield from 6.00% in 1993 to 7.09% in 2020. Current interest
serial bonds are priced at par to yield from 6.00% in 1993 to
6.95% in 2004. There are $12.9 million of term bonds priced
at par to yield 7% in 2010. There are $37.5 million of 7.05%
term bonds priced at 99 1/2 to yield 7.09% in 2020. The bonds
are insured and rated triple-A by Moody's and S&amp;P.
                                                                                                       

                          MORTGAGE
                                                                                                       

   Federal National Mortgage Association -- $500 million of
real estate mortgage investment conduit securities is being
offered in 21 classes by Salomon Brothers Inc. The offering,
Series 1990-99, is backed by Fannie Mae 9 1/2% securities.
Details on prices and yields weren't immediately available.
                                                                                                       

                          EUROBONDS
                                                                                                       

   Furukawa Co. (Japan) -- 150 million Swiss francs ($109
million) of privately placed notes due Aug. 15, 1995, with
equity-purchase warrants. Fixed 4% coupon at par via Credit
Suisse. Guarantee by Dai-Ichi Kangyo Bank. Exercise period
from Aug. 27, 1990, to Aug. 4, 1995. Terms fixed Aug. 27.
Exercise price of the warrants will be refixed at a
not-yet-specified date if the share price at the time is
below the exercise price. Call at issuer's option from Aug.
15, 1993, at 101, declining by 1/2 point annually.
   Ford Credit Australia Ltd. (U.S. parent) -- 75 million
Australia dollars (US$58.9 million) of 14 1/2% bonds due Aug.
29, 1995, priced at 101.75 to yield 14.57% less fees, via
Hambros Bank Ltd. Guaranteed by Ford Motor Credit. Fees 2.
   Postipankki (Finland) -- 75 million Swiss francs of 7 1/8%
public bonds due Sept. 7, 2005, priced at 101 3/4 via Bank J.
Henry Schroder AG. Call from Sept. 7, 2000, at par.
</TEXT>
