   Business Brief -- Munich Re AG:
   Year's Group Profit Rose;
   Dividend to Remain Stable
</HL>
<DATE>
07/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   G.MUV
</CO>
<LP>
   Muenchener Rueckversicherungs-Gesellschaft (Munich Re) AG
said that fiscal 1990 group net profit rose from year-earlier
levels and that the company will leave its dividend unchanged
at 10 Deutsche marks ($6.18) a share.
   The large, West German reinsurance group didn't provide
detailed earnings data, but said premium income from
reinsurance business rose 1.6% to 12.6 billion marks in the
fiscal year that ended June 30 from 12.4 billion marks the
year before
</LP>
<TEXT>
   "Overall, the fiscal 1990 result will prove to be
satisfactory," Munich Re said, adding that the strength of
the Deutsche mark had a negative impact on premium income
development. Without currency translation effects, total
group premium income actually increased more than 4%.
