<HL>
   Business Brief -- James River Corp.:
   European Affiliate Purchases
   Two Greek Tissue Concerns
</HL>
<DATE>
07/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   JR
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   James River Corp., Richmond, Va., said its European
affiliate JA/MONT N.V. bought Cartellas S.A. and Achaia S.A.,
two tissue companies in Athens, Greece, formerly owned by the
Panopoulos family.
   Terms were not disclosed. The two companies, which market
under the Delica brand name in Greece, posted combined 1989
sales of $40.7 million. Sales for Cartellas were $33.5
million; sales for Achaia were $7.2 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The two companies combined represent the second largest
tissue producer in the Greek market, with a 15 to 20% share,
the company said.
   The acquisition is the first by JA/MONT V.A., a joint
venture formed this year that combined James River's European
tissue interests with those of Gruppo Ferruzzi of Italy and
Nokia Corp. of Finland. The joint venture expects sales of
$1.6 billion in 1990.
</TEXT>
