   Business Brief -- Adia Services Inc.:
   Second-Quarter Net Drops
   At Employment Concern
</HL>
<DATE>
07/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ADIA Z.ADI
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Adia Services Inc. said a sluggish economy caused
second-quarter earnings to dip slightly, to $5 million, or 40
cents a share, compared with $5.4 million, or 43 cents a
share in the year-earlier period. Revenue for the quarter
rose 13% to $166.6 million from $148 million a year earlier.
   For the first six months, the Menlo Park, Calif.,
company's net income was $10 million, or 80 cents a share,
compared with $10.3 million, or 83 cents a share in the
year-earlier period. Revenue for the six months were $327.5
million compared with $289.9 million for the prior fiscal
year.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Switzerland-based Adia S.A., one of the world's largest
temporary employment agencies, owns a 66% stake in Adia
Services.
