</IN>
<LP>
   Thailand's national carrier, Thai Airways International
Ltd., reported record earnings for the first six months of
the fiscal year.
   The airline made 4.1415 billion baht ($161.5 million) in
pretax profits for the period, the company said. That
represented a 17% increase over the year-earlier period and
the highest half-year profit in the airline's 30 years of
operation.
